  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This randomised, controlled study aims to evaluate the impact of endoscopic assessment, and
      adjustment of therapy, after surgery in patients with Crohn's disease. The primary endpoint
      is the severity of endoscopic recurrence. In addition, tissue will be collected for
      microbiological and immunological analysis.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
